<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="f22ae528-1934-5c42-8c18-84389bcd4fe6" activityNameId="290aca84-c16b-42b6-9b58-b38a7a0376c2" parentActivityId="62a6c46f-90d6-4cb2-b39d-15e83ad3f876" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1" energyValues="0">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">carbon monoxide production</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en"/>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This report assumes that CO is produced from partial combustion of heavy heating oil. The inventory is based on assumed production figures from a planned plant. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">It is assumed that the produced hydrogen is combusted and provides the required steam. Water emissions from combustion are included.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Other production pathways were not included, due to a lack of data.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]</text>
        </generalComment>
        <tag>ConvertedDataset</tag>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
